UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105018822741?origin=resultslist
AB  - Focusing on the multi-equipment cooperative scheduling problem of U-shaped automated container terminals (MECSP-UACT), this paper investigates the dynamic cooperative optimisation of automated guided vehicles (AGVs), external trucks (ETs), and yard cranes (YCs). Existing scheduling models diverge significantly from real-world logistics systems, limiting their practical application. High-fidelity digital twin (DT) environment accurately replicates logistics processes and provides an effective platform for algorithm training and validation. A DT-based collaborative scheduling environment using deep reinforcement learning (DRL) is proposed. A three-layer ‘Physical-Twin-Decision’ architecture is built. The physical layer collects real-time data from AGV locations, ET appointments, and YC statuses via IoT. The twin-layer model uses the U-ACT as a training environment to ensure model completeness. The decision layer uses Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) for offline training and online scheduling, addressing real-time scheduling challenges. Historical freight data from a southeastern hub port is used for experiments. Results demonstrate the method’s applicability under complex and dynamic conditions. © 2025 Informa UK Limited, trading as Taylor & Francis Group.
