AB  - The Pieter Schelte vessel reached the Port of Rotterdam on January 8, 2015 from the Daewoo Shipbuilding and Marine Engineering shipyard, South Korea. The vessel, designed and built by Allseas, will take off for her first decommissioning project for Shell in Norway. Over the next five months the 382 meter long and 124 meter wide vessel will be completed at the Maasvlakte 2. The works consist among others of the instalment of 16 lifing beams, 65 meters long, that together with the hydraulic claws, will lift and carry the superstructure of an oil or gas platform weighing up to 48,000 tons at once.
