AB  - This paper addresses the challenges in target recognition and measurement algorithms for various operational equipment requiring pose detection and position measurement in port environments. It proposes a simulation platform based on digital twin technology for visual measurement in port automation equipment. The platform includes the design of virtual fixed-focus and zoom cameras, effectively simulating the imaging characteristics of real cameras. Additionally, this paper designed a virtual measurement sample generation framework capable of automatically generating diverse and annotated datasets of port targets. Experimental results show that when training with a mixed dataset containing both virtual and real images, the YOLO v5 network achieves a mean average precision (mAP) 40.24% higher than that trained solely on real images. Furthermore, tests using YOLO v8 and Faster R-CNN algorithms demonstrated that the mAP improved by 31.36% and 35.78%, respectively, when using the mixed dataset. These results prove that the proposed visual measurement simulation platform significantly enhances the generalization capability and robustness of algorithms for measuring port targets using visual cameras. © 2025 IEEE.
