AB  - To address the collision avoidance problem of automated stacking cranes (ASCs) in the automated container terminal, this paper provides a collision-free simulation framework for ASCs. The framework is constructed based on Spatio-temporal information and enables the effective collision avoidance of multiple ASCs even when different path planning algorithms considering only obstacle avoidance are embedded into the framework. Finally, the effectiveness of the collision-free simulation framework is demonstrated by embedding the A * algorithm and Ant Colony algorithm into the framework.  © 2022 IEEE.
